Dragon Temple Map by Sundered Dragon begins here.

"Adds a new sub area to Pirate Island accessable only Dragon Breeders to the flexible survival game."

Section 1  - Moon Pool

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Moon Pool	"Moon Pool"

Moon Pool is a room. It is fasttravel.
Moon Pool is private.
Description of Moon Pool is "[moonpooldesc]".
the scent of Moon Pool is "Bracing, yet salty with undercurrents of ancient rock and potential.".

to say moonpooldesc:
	if Morale of Arlene < 10:
		say "     Roughly and hastily cleaved open by the Nazokaazthur, the circular Moonpool's raw basaltic black edges, alongside its vaulted ceiling, are still covered in deep claw marks, and pitted with a sprawling spiderweb of cracks left by the sea titans['] excavation as they tunneled their way north towards the temple proper. Though a paltry effort has been made to smooth the icy stale floor and high walls, many of the surfaces are still uneven, in place small pits still mar the jet black rock. At times though, odd inclusions can be seen peeking through the surface, whether they be of fossil or mineral you can't be certain, nor can the precious few cultists you have find the time to properly excavate them. Instead, they've busied themselves setting up small cylindrical electric ";
		If "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "no larger than a tea light held within rough sconces made of rusty unidentifiable metal likely found upon the Quiet Sandbar that have been shoddily hammered into the general shape of sea dragons paws, or maws. Though their faint cloud white glow barely illuminates much of the room, and a small, hastily craved memorial tucked into the southern most edges of the area that reads: [italic type]In memory of Jenny and Boots[roman type]. Their weak radiance nevertheless highlights the calm crisp blue waters of the Moon Pool proper's border as the tiny waves affectionately lap at the stone.";
	[else if Morale of Arlene >= 11 and Morale of Arlene < 20:
		say"    Worn slightly smoother by the passage of the cult's human members and mighty draconic protectors, as they ferry supplies to the deeper sections of your nascent temple, the Moon Pool's floor has lost much of its rough qualities. As a few of the larger pits left behind by initial works of the dragon brother have been filled with small pebbles taken from the depths as your cult hews its way deeper into the cold womb of the earth. Many of the worthless inclusions have slowly been smooth, or chiseled out by hand or claw, yet a few instances of fossilized spiraling sea shells or the odd nameless deep sea creature are allowed to remain, for the moment. The walls though are still as unfinished as ever, for your people lack the tools and materials necessary to set up the proper scaffolding necessary to reach and repair the deep rents in the lustrous black stone. While the simple";
		if"Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say"torches";
		else:
			say"lanterns ";
		say"have been replaced with more industrial L.E.Ds covered in spherical pyrex orbs."; 
		say"      Their holders too have been re-polished, then worked into more uniformed patterns, yet their design leaves much to be desired. As their surfaces are still warped, or chipped from the overeager hammering of your supplicants while their likeness to a proper dragon's imperial maw or beastly paws is… tangential at best. Interestingly, your cultists have taken it upon themselves to festoon these light sources with sets of cleverly placed circular mirrors which redirect their luminance towards the Moon Pool and away from much of the unfinished ceiling, shrouding it in the deepest shadow. Bathed in their gentle white rays, the azure water and onyx stone gleam all the brighter, meanwhile, the rough entrance situated toward the north leading towards your temple proper has been carved into a simple pyramid shape, yet many of the clawmarks left behind by the Naxokaazthur have been left behind as a reminder of the true power of the mighty dragon brothers.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 21 and Morale of Arlene < 30:
		say"      Thanks to the tireless work of you thralls and followers, the last of the rough edges and uneven surfaces dotting the floor of the Moon Pool have finally been smoothed away. Though the gashes left behind by the Naxokaazthur remain, your cultists have taken it upon themselves to clean and polish them in reverence to the mighty sea titans. While a number of your more artistically inclined supplicants have taken it upon themselves to preserve the fossil inclusion dotting the floor and walls, even now the polished ghostly spiraling images of ancient sea life shimmer along the dark slate stone like muted stars in the available light. The scones too have been refined further with fresh metal taken from the Quiet Sandbar, although some of the original material anchoring the ;"
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say"torches";
		else:
			say"lanterns ";
		say"yet remains, the new holder are with hair more defined as fierce articulate draconic maws and chiseled predatory paws dotting the walls serve as crude yet effective markers of how far the cult has come in so short a time.";
		say"     The L.E.Ds as well have been swapped out with for stronger higher lumens grow lights, and a number of purple Afghan poppies and Snapdragons situated in terracotta pots painted a rich velvety black have been arrayed along the path leading toward the temple's main hall. The glass mirrors have been cut and adjusted to focus the light upon the main path and bath the plants in a pleasingly pale light. Thanks to some clever positioning, only the ceiling remains cloaked in shadow as your follower still lacks the tools or numbers necessary to finish planing the vaulted roof. While the azure depths of the Mool Pool gleams all the brighter in the bone white ambiance of L.E.Ds, to your eye the tranquil water have almost taken a gemstone like quality that is further enhanced by pristine reflection dancing upon the lustrous black rock framing your temple's entrance.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 31 and Morale of Arlene < 40:
		say"     With the gradual influx of abyssal wealth, your cultist have taken it upon themselves to affect some minor improvement to the Mool Pool as they slowly widen the aquatic gateway a into spherical effigy of a Sea Tyrant's eye to accommodate the increased traffic to and from your sanctum beneath the waves. A thin series of steps too have also been carved into the slate leading towards the pyramid shaped entrance to the main hall. By necessity they vary in size, ranging from short human sized platforms, to vaulted artifice suited to the proud stride of your tauric young. The stone walkway too has been further polished with wax bartered from the nascent black market at the warehouse district and now shimmers in the  ;"
		if"Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say"torch";
		else:
			say"lantern ";
		say"light. Under the increasingly expert care of your followers, the spiraling fossils lining the floors and walls have also polished to mirror-like finish. While the sconces have been further improved by a number of former metal works who have taken it upon themselves to enhance the quality of them by subtly chiseling in tasteful scales pattern upon the near life like renditions of the draconic maws and paws clasping the vibrant spherical L.E.D light ringing the Moon Pool.";
		say"    The series of mirrors placed behind them remain largely unchanged, though a few have been sneakily hidden around the Moon Pool to reflect [']waste['] light back upon the plants dotting the area. Added by the nanites, the near constant exposure to the grow lights, and guano retrieved from the island proper, the purple Afghan Poppies and alabaster Snapdragons are steadily outgrowing their potters. Already thin cracks can be seen forming along their painted surface, as the plant's impressive root ball strains against their temporary housing while their stalks struggle to support the blooms. In time, they will need to be replaced but for now, this little touch of green, purple, and white nevertheless serves as a pleasant accent to the pristine azure waters of the Moon Pool and muted luminance glow of the polished slate reflecting in the available light.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 41 and Morale of Arlene < 50:
		say"     Buoyed by the growing abundance of the precious resources dredged from the depths, your followers have begun decorating the Moon Pool with some of the cult's excess sea gold and meteoric gemstones. As they have taken to filling the deep claw marks scattered across the floor left over by the Naxokaazthur's initial excavations with pure gold, though some bemoan their loss, others are more than glad to be rid of the tripping hazard they possessed. Efforts though have been taken to preserve those few lining the entrance way situated to the north with a simple lacquering of lucite. The scones have been bejeweled in carefully chiseled flakes of moonstone and aquamarine along their scales and claws of the paws shaped lantern holders. Meanwhile, the yearning maw patterned holsters have been bedazzled in shimmering garnet and lustrous mother of pearl. Still, out of respect for the senior members, the original metal remains largely untouched beyond the odd bit of maintenance to keep the salty air from eroding it further.";
		say"     The mirrors too remain unaltered, save the occasion readjustments to better direct the grow lights towards the impromptu garden blooming along the central walkway. Positively glutted on lumens, alongside the constant influx of guano taken from the surface, the quick growing nanite enhanced planets tower over the average human. As such your cultists have taken to fashioning a simple, yet sturdy arch out of bone white driftwood to help bear their weight while the open lattice work covering it allows some of the larger flowers to dangle overhead and lightly perfume the area with a pleasing flora scent. These vibrant blooms offer a lovely backdrop to the glassy smooth azure waters of the Moon Pool proper and its gleaming slate ring it. Meanwhile, your cultists have, at last, begun working on the ceiling, limited though it may be, as some of the architectly minded members of your cult have voiced their concerns about the carelessly mining away with little thought to the structural integrity of the temple. Instead, a number of tritium lights have been carefully arranged amidst the craggy stone like miniature constellations. A feature many of your subterranean followers are thankful for, as few wish to brave the surface without an escort of your tauric young or Seradovah thralls. Even now several of your gravid followers happily sit about about the Moon Pool's edge as they soak their ankle in the cool water while gazing at the lights twinkling overhead.";
	else if Morale of Arlene <= 51:
		say"     Overflowing with wealth and fecund abundance, the once austere Moon Pool could now easily be mistaken for the entrance to some high-end night club or annex of a private resort as the constantly polished and maintained stale stone alongside the gold inlays covering the claw marks left by the Naxokaazthur shines with a near mirror-like finish. Even the walls have taken on a pleasant, reflective quality your cultists have come to appreciate as scores of jovial mothers-to-be leisurely strut about the area, flaunting and admiring their curves while wide-eyed novices look on with envy. Special care has been taken to preserve the fossils lining the area as the odd spiral pattern of the ancient sea creatures are fetching in their own right. The sconces too have been treated to another round of lapidary work as the brilliant moon stone lining the draconic talons have had wondrously realistic scale patterns engraved upon them. While the once metal fangs affixed to the yearning reptilian maws have been swapped with real ivory culled from the depths by your priestess.";
		say "     Though the original metal frames placed down by your original cultists remains intact, a coating of preservative black paint has been added to ensure it never again rusts. Little has been changed with the mirror dotting the area beyond the occasional adjustments to account for increased size of the poppies and Snapdragon arrayed around the path leading north towards the entrance to the temple proper. As the now repotted planets have, despite all expectations, have grown into a vast canopy of purple and white flowers over the bone white lattice archway that fills the immediate area beneath it with a soft floral scent. Owing to the increased popularity and affinity of your cultist's affinity for gravidity, the Moon Pool's calm azure water has steadily become a preferred place for your vivacious brood mothers as they lounge upon about its edges, ready and eager to greet the newest members of your cult should any arrive.";]

Moon Pool is south of Dragon's Causeway.



Section 2 - Dragon's Causeway

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Dragon's Causeway	"Dragon's Causeway"

Dragon's Causeway is a room.
Description of Dragon's Causeway is "[TMHD]".
the scent of Dragon's Causeway is "The scents of cold earth and reptilian ambitions waft through the area.".

to say TMHD:
	if Morale of Arlene < 10:
		say "     More of a void in the belly of the earth than a true hall, the rough central junction leading to the rest of temple ground is hardly befitting a dragon of your stature, yet considering the speed at which the Naxokaazthur and Seradovah excavated it, you and your cult will have to make do for now. Still with the guidance of your human supplicants and priestess, Tiamat's mindless thralls have done an admirable job clearing five distinct pathways into the slate leading to The Cultist's Chamber to the west, the larder and kitchen to the northwest, your personal hoard to the north, your Priestess's bedroom to the east, Tiamat's Chapel to the southeast, and Moon Pool to the south. Much work still needs to be done as roughly chiseled and dragon breath hewed stone is far from leveled, and only a scant few cylindrical eclectic ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "affixed to a number of load bearing slate pillars with scavenged bit of copper taken from the Quiet Sandbar ringing the pathways bathe the area in a pale bone-white light.";
		say "     Beyond their hollow glow, the area is little more than a craggy rent in the ground that your followers dare not venture into without good cause. Lacking both the tools or numbers needed to clear the remaining rubble and bereft of the Naxokaazthur's aid in further excavation for fear they might undermine the nascent temple, you doubt they will be able to improve the area further. Perhaps your priestess can offer some advice on how to remedy this situation.";
	[else if Morale of Arlene >= 11 and Morale of Arlene < 20:
		say "   As the days wear on and your cult's numbers begin to rise, the main is slowly becoming worthy of its name, if only by sheer virtue of attrition as constant foot falls of the temple's human inhabitants and your draconic spawn, the pathways leading to The Cultist's Chamber to the west, the larder and kitchen to the northwest, your personal hoard to the north, your Priestess's bedroom to the east, The Chapel to the south east, and Moon Pool to the south have at last been made slightly serviceable. Though far from being planed or refined, your barefooted cultists are now more willing to begin leading the Seradovah in the monotonous task of excavating the crags pillar ringing the main path. Nevertheless, the going is slow and even with addition of more powerful L.E.D ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "encased in sturdy pyrex globes which have been hastily anchored to the long rows of slate pillars lining the main walkway with reclaimed flotsam bolts. It's however unlikely your small band of loyalists will be able to get more done in a timely fashion.";
		say "     That said, the rough primal aesthetic of the cavern is in some ways fitting, nevertheless, without more tools, warm bodies, and expertise needed to assist them. Work is once more stalling out as the few humans and their Seradovah workers assigned to this area hem and haw over how best to cleave away some stalagmites stubbornly clinging to the slate floor, or pain painstakingly try to widen the rough opening in jet black stone leading the rest of the temple. Thankfully, your fertile priestess, and the lovely additions your flight shi produces, are more than eager to assist you in expanding the cult's numbers. You need only pay hir, or perhaps some of your delectable followers who have earned the earned the right to carry your regal offspring a visit...";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 21 and Morale of Arlene < 30:
		say "     At long last, the final section of rough stone has cleared and the rubble disposed of, though the hall remains a rather spartan space, the pathways are nonetheless blessedly free of any obstruction. The load bearing slate pillars have slowly begun to be smoothed and shaped like ornate candle candlesticks. A number of recesses have been careful carved into the native slate along the cardinal points into which the electric "; 
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say " have been anchored along with their globular pyrex domes. The entrances leading to The Cultist's Chamber to the west, the larder and kitchen to the northwest, your personal hoard to the north, your Priestess's bedroom to the east, The Chapel to the south east, and Moon Pool to the south have been widened into identical pyramid shapes while there edges have been polished smooth to a near mirror like sheen.";
		say "     Meanwhile a few larger pieces of workable slate have been carefully arrayed about the corners of the now cuboid hall and are currently in the process of being carved into benches and crude lumpy idols of five headed draconic goddess Tiamat. Mixed in between them though are a few lesser but ever more articulate effigies of your coldblooded splendor, though fetching, the skills of the cultists leaves much to be desired and their proportions are slightly off too. Yet the sight of your magnificence in various states of repose and gravidity is flattering in its own right, perhaps in time as their skills improve, or when new members gifted with talent necessary are attracted by your regal spawn during the next foyer to the city someone might be able to affect the improvements. For now, the heartfelt images dedicated to your draconic personage will have to do, though were you in a [']giving['] you could alway pay your lustful priestess and budding follower a visit to show them your appreciation for their tireless work in refining your temple.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 31 and Morale of Arlene < 40:
		say "    Buoyed by the cults' growing numbers and greater access to the spoils of the briny depths, your followers have taken it upon themselves to begin polished the umbral slate walls and of the Main Hall to a sleek sheen. Though maintaining it has proven difficult as the uncaring bite of you and your swelling flight's talons often undoes much of the little humans effort, your loyalists never slack in their diligence as trains of neophytes routinely prowl the walkways at all hours to effect repair when needed. To their credit, your brood does their best to avoid scuffing the floor and even pauses to quietly praise the works of the little humans in honoring their draconic masters while they go about their tasks. Meanwhile, the many pillars ringing the pathways leading towards the Cultist's Chamber to the west, the larder and kitchen to the northwest, your personal hoard to the north, your Priestess's bedroom to the east, The Chapel to the south east, and Moon Pool to the south are now host to a small number of craving dedicated your spawn and your cultist's growing affinity gravidity."; 
		say "     Most are little more than childish stick figure or crude graffiti depicting your fecund follower fawning over their plush bumps, or worshiping your broods exotic anatomy, yet a few of show a bit of promise and improvement as neither you nor your priestess are in any hurry to put a stop to the practice. The benches and idols decorating the Main Hall's edges too have become slightly more ornate as the benches have been hewed into simply blocky structures with cheap red cotton sheets thrown over them. While the five headed effigies of the dragon goddess are steadily gaining definition as the formerly lump renditions of her draconic form have slowly evolved into more slender, bestial figure, though it still scale or eyes. More attention though has been paid to your own icons, as your obsessive followers as they've begun adding more creative flourish like scores of your human worship bowing at your paws, or proudly display themselves to you with legs spread wide in offering.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 41 and Morale of Arlene < 50:
		say "     As your cult's tides rise so too does the opulence of the Main Hall as sturdy red carpet made of some unknown textile has placed down along the pathways leading towards the Cultist's Chamber to the west, the larder and kitchen to the northwest, your personal hoard to the north, your Priestess's bedroom to the east, The Chapel to the south east, and Moon Pool to the south. Rather durable and voluminous, the carpet is a welcomed addition to your barefooted followers as despite their devotion to the cause, the bracing chill wafting out from the Moon Pool kept the ground icy cold. Still, your diligent novices, ever eager to earn the praise of their betters, still prowl the walks as do their best to keep the paths clean, and to entice your brood. More than once, you've spotted one such lustful human on their hands and knees, cunts flushed with need as they shamelessly offer themselves to your impressive progeny. True to their lineage and purpose, your virile descendants are more than happy to oblige these offers and pluck their chosen from the floor before vanishing to their private warrens deep below the cultist's chambers.";
		say "      The artwork circumscribing the various the sleek, curvy slate pillars to has grown all the more tastefully lewd as days of practice, and the odd pointer from the doe-eyed neophytes has further honed their craft. As the once simple caricatures of your loyalist's gravid figures facing Main Hall's walls have slowly been molded into a sprawling mosaic of plush and buxom breeders flaunting their milky motherly bodies. While the images carved along the sections facing the pathways now shows the journey of your followers as they take their steps out of the Moon Pool, to their first blessed coupling with your brood, and the wondrous change to their bodies as they ripen with your spawn. The benches dotting the edges of the hall have become more ornate as tactful scale patterns evocative of a Sea Tyrant's sinuous limbs and powerful paws have been inscribed along their border and leg that seem to gleam like jet in the bone white glow of the ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches. ";
		else:
			say "lanterns. ";
		say "Simple red velvet cushions have also been placed down, for the comfort of your lovely breeders and their apprentices. Meanwhile, the idols dedicated toTiamat and you have been further honed then painted in vivid detail."; 
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 51:
		say "    Resplendent and opulent, the work on the Main Hall has reached the zenith of what your cultist's can achieve as the stonework shines with a waxy smooth onyx finish. The carpet has been expanded to only cover the pathways towards the Cultist's Chamber to the west, the larder and kitchen to the northwest, your personal hoard to the north, your Priestess's bedroom to the east, The Chapel to the south east, and Moon Pool to the south but the benches as well. While the lustful image cast upon the artful slate pillar depicting your journey for awkward initiates to confident curvy broodmares have been inlaid with pearl, chocolate diamond, ruby, aquamarine and citrine. Their proportions of you senior cultist decorating the outer section of main path have grown all the more exaggerated as bellies dominate their plush well-bred bodies while a bead of opal 'milk' stream from their colossal tis perched atop them. A few of the recess used to hold the globular ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "have been slightly reworked around lurid deceptions of your pregnant cultist's glowing middles.";
		say "     All the while, carefully cut sections of sapphire been affix to the scale patterns lining the scatter about the hall and extra padding to insure the comfort of your tireless breeders and the eager novices waiting as playfully show off their bountiful to your spawn as they passerby. Following in paw steps, your descents need little urging in selecting a fresh mate, you can tell they're enjoying the of the lewd humans shamelessly flaunting themselves before them. The icons dedicated to Tiamat have been expanded into a mural of sorts depicting your first meeting with the goddess's avatar-to-be and your ascension to dragon. True, some artistic license was taken with your former selves proportions and form, the sight of your change still brings a proud smirk to your face. Your paint idols too have more austenations as once simple depictions of gravid grace and tauric form in lewd repose are now joined by pictures of your cultists and priestess basking in your splendor as they off their ripe bodies to you.";]

Dragon's Causeway is north of Moon Pool.
Dragon's Causeway is east of Cultist's Chambers.
Dragon's Causeway is southeast of Mess Hall.
Dragon's Causeway is south of Treasury.
Dragon's Causeway is west of Priestess's Chamber.
Dragon's Causeway is northwest of Tiamat's Chapel.

Section 3 - Cultist's Chambers

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Cultist's Chambers	"Cultist's Chambers"

Cultist's Chambers is a room.
Description of Cultist's Chambers is "[cultistschambersdesc]".
the scent of Cultist's Chambers is "Ripe with the coiling aroma of feminine need and coldblooded purpose.".

to say cultistschambersdesc:
	if Morale of Arlene < 10:
		say "     Rugged and spartan, the row of simple 'cells' hastily cleaved into this vast and oft times jaded slate passage are home to your devoted human followers, with little resource to spare and even few bodies to carry out necessary work needed to improve their meager conditions. To their credit, your loyalists bear this harshness without complaint and seem to view this as a test of their faith. Mercifully, the Naxokaazthur and your priestess have furnished them with simple bundles of fur likely taken from the initial conquest of the island to serve as bedding. In their free time, your resourceful followers have slowly been gathering bits of driftwood alongside rusty square nails from the Quiet Sandbar during their rare trips to the surface and fashioning them into crude tables or dressers. A smattering of puny gun-metal-gray hand-crank-powered ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "salvaged from the supplies leftover from your cargo ship raid have been haphazardly hammered into walls at random intervals and bathe the area in a yellow-orange glow. Somewhere, beyond the reach of this paltry illumination, is a passageway leading down to your spawn's personal lair and the Seradovah holding cells along with impromptu birthing chambers. Out of respect for your children's privacy, and in no great hurry to witness the arrival of your latest descendants, you have elected to avoid visiting the lower depths unless absolutely necessary.";
	[else if Morale of Arlene >= 11 and Morale of Arlene < 20:
		say "      Aided by the steady trickle of new members, not to mention resources, the dual efforts of your cultist and prolific progeny have steadily hacked the rough unfinished stone floors and walls. Though nowhere near level, the seemingly endless rows of cultist cells lining this sprawling passage are at least slightly more livable, not to mention comfortable as the lingering chunk of jagged slate stone has cleared away. Still, your hardy cultist's have precious few belongs to their name as their auster chambers are mostly host simple futon made from the fuzzy pelts looted during the islands conquest alongside a smatter of emergency blanket dredged out of storage from the various containers you liberated from the stricken supply ship. While a mix of adhoc furniture built from flotsam found on the Quiet Sandbar, and leftover equipment looted from the black shipping crates you passed some time ago adorns many of their rooms. Though the quality varies, your scrappy followers are steadily becoming better at their craft as they constantly tweak and improve their living spaces in their free time. As evident by the cunning addition of reflective sea polished glass to the halls and their rooms meant to reflect the available light.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "    Mixed in among your tiny band of loyal followers are the playful faces of the Husky Bitches your followers adopt during your raid of the slave kennels. Though of little assistance in the great work, their presence is still comforting to your followers and a few have taken to inviting them to sleep in the quarters at night. Not that you blame, the cuddly canines no doubt make excellent bed warmers, or lovely playmates in those rare instances your spawn are otherwise occupied. The more maternally minded pups have proven themselves to be wonderful wet nurses during the event your budding breeders are unable to properly feed some of their larger clutches. Or convenient fuck toys for your fertile followers when the lewd urges brought on by the wondrous cocktail of corrupted nanites laced with their motherly hormones course through them begin to bubble to the surface. More than once, you walked past one such couple of your ponderously pregnant follower laying on her back while one or more husky girl attends her blush folds, or pampers her tender bump.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 2:
			say "      Spurred on by your domineering and hedonistic example, your more fertile and senior members of your cult have started to [']adopt['] many of the newer and less fecund individuals as handmaidens or apprentices. Though most appear to use their peers as little more than doting servants or personally masseuses fit only to pamper and feed their eggs while they luxuriate in their blissful state, or serve as go between for them and your virile spawn in the fleeting moments betwixt clutches. A few still do their best to instill within these novices a deep love for brood motherdom or guide them through their first clutch as they take their first steps towards becoming a proper breeder. Yet others, issue taking on helpers, and instead have begun cultivating a small following of draconic regulars from the growing ranks of your. The more successful among them are occasionally invited to join your brood in the lower lever and are rarely seen without a tummy full of eggs or protective cohort of dragons in their wake.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 3:
			say "     Thanks to their proximity to your spawn and your own loving attention, a number of your cultists have started to adopt a few draconic traits, though at times they are hardly noticeable. The sight of your loyal follower draconic eyes gleaming in the distance, or the rare shimmer of their scales rarely falls to put a smile on your face. True, you noticed a certain stratification blossoming among their ranks as the more draconic of your worshipers have begun to command more respect from there. What's more, a great deal of the untouched humans have started to display a degree of reverence for them as they seek to emulate their peers['] behavior or worship these ascendant's bountiful bodies. Yet this development is still far from worrying as only the most devout and breedable among them seem capable of ascension, you can see little harm in allowing the practice to especially if doing ultimately serves hurry their final transformation to dragondom.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 21 and Morale of Arlene < 30:
		say "       Bolstered by the welcome influx of followers and materials, the living conditions of your cultist has improved immensely as the area has taken on the same lustrous onyx sheen dotting the temple grounds. Aided by its polished reflective surface, the ponderously lengthy passage arrayed with cultist's cell is more well lit than ever as the soft yellow-orange glow of the many ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "decorating the walls has pushed back the gloom all the to the edges of the massive staircase leading down to the lower level hosting your spawn and Seradovah. While the ready access to materials dredged from the depths along the increased number of the cult has attracted, has allowed your followers to fashion fully functional beds large enough to accommodate them, and the odd lucky wyrm of the evening. Their furniture too, though still comprised of reclaimed wood and metal is at of a quality befitting of your cultist as the thrift among have managed to trade the odd bauble for proper tools, paints, and preservatives necessary to shape the various desks, tables, and chairs into commendable works of amateur art. Likely inspired by your reptilian splendor, most are home to simple, yet heart draconic motifs like the odd scale pattern along their edges, or large paw-like shapes chiseled into their feet.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "     The number of Husky Bitches has slowly grown too though you suspect they were likely snuck in by your followers during their trips to the mainland, or gifted by some of your affectionate spawn. Regardless, their smiley faces and warm snuggly dispossession has earned them a permanent place at your cultists side as each of your cultist abodes['] is home to at least of the subby canines. More than a little proud at their ability to tame these weak infected, many of your loyalists have taken to fashioning leashes and collars to better display their power over them as they walk them through the halls. Ever the dutiful creatures, the lusty huskies have come to serve the cultist in others ways too, as their reluctance to play with their pets has completely worn away. As such it's becoming increasingly common to catch sight of the happy huskies and their mistress frolicking atop their new beds together in their off hours. A service few of your more brood-minded followers could do without as their infatuation with their ripening bodies, so to does their desire for the soothing kiss of their pets tongue upon their blushing petals.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 2:
			say "     Though as time wears on, your more dominant and fecund followers ever eager to follow in your example have begun to tighten their control over the less productive members of the cult. Not that you are of any mind to stop them, as their emulation of your ways is only natural and their tireless devotion towards breeding more dragons for the cause is a small price to pay for putting up with their increasingly sedentary lifestyle. Already many are blossoming to truly curvy and voluptuous broodmares with few concerns other than their next meal, and their bottomless passion to serve as hosts for your progeny. Other more altruistic members of the cult, still take it upon themselves to care for and educate the newest members about the proper means of pleasing your spawn or walking them through their first pregnancy, yet as time goes on their number seem to be shrinking. As for the brave cultists who have turned their backs up the others, and instead work to earn the permanent patronage of a few loyal dragons. Their influence is slowly growing despite their tiny number, as none would dare challenge their will openly.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 3:
			say "    Your cultists are gradually showing signs of shedding their prior human forms as much to their delight as more of them now sport slitted draconic eyes alongside the odd patch of glittering scales. Others though, graced with sleek spaded tails or cute aquamarine horns growing from their foreheads. Sadly, not all of you loyalists appear to have been thusly blessed by the touch of yours and your spawns lovely nanites. Why though, no one is certain, yet this has deterred them from the path as the poor baseliners remain committed to expanding your flight, regardless of if they ascend or not. Yet has not the stopped the stratification between your quai-dragon and human follower from deepening as your ascending loyalists are steadily amassing groups of eager novices to serve or care for them so they better focus on their  A few of your more kindhearted dragons-to-be though, have instead taken it upon themselves to aid their less fortunate peers in reaching the same heights either through group pray or by helping then attract draconic mates.";
		else if Morale of Arlene >= 41 and Morale of Arlene < 50:
			say "      Nearly drowning in raw materials and abyssal riches, considerable effort has been taken to put down a cushy layer of downy soft red carpeting along the expansive hall containing your cultist room's. A feature your barefooted breeders have welcomed with open arms as despite being hardened by the apocalypse, the bracing chill of the now glassy smooth slate temple grounds remains as oppressive as ever. Their furniture too is now an eclectic mix of artful handmade tables, chairs, and bed frame emblazoned with draconic motifs, along modern plastic trunks and dressers bartered from the mainland. Many of the ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "have slowly been replaced with grow lights powered rechargeable solar cells, thanks to this new light source. A number of sweet smelling salvias, hardy marigolds, and aromatic mints have been imported to give the cultist rooms a touch more color.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "     The number of their Husky Bitch pets has continued to climb as your cultists skill in training these subby slut puppies improved over time as each of your loyalist's abodes now has at least two adorable canines. Under their instructive care, these intelligent ferals have become quite adept caretakers and companions for your cultists, and some have been taught to cook or clean for their loving mistresses, allowing them to focus on the all important task of whelping your spawn. Even now, most of your loyalists are happily sporting glowing bumps, or spend their time being fawn over their flirtatious pets. The equally motherly huskies seem to enjoy their mistress's needy condition and the chance to spoil them by the lovely massaging the owner's ankles, or attending to their bubbly nanite laced lust. As the shameless husky girls zealously attend to their mistress's needs with but a glance, and it's not uncommon to see a group of cultists sharing a meal while their loyal lovingly eat them out under the table.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 2:
			say "      While the tastes and needs of your most domineering, hedonistic cultists have only grown all the more decadent as they eagerly follow in yours and to a certain extent, the goddess's example by binding much the newer and less fertile members to the service. These plush fecund broodmare rarely leave their rooms expect to be carried to the nursery to deliver their latest clutch. Otherwise their sole focus is the enticement of your spawn, and quenching their broods ravenous hunger, as such teams of cowed novices can often be scurrying through the halls carrying platter of food. Still, more dot upon their curvy better bodies in the vain hope some measure of their fertility will somehow rub off on them, or that they might attract the attention of some virile wyrms one day. Meanwhile, the bold humans dwelling in the lower levels and their draconic mates['] command over the others has continued to grow as well as the hold the brash cultists have over your malleable young. Another time, you might have spoken out, yet even you are forced to begrudgingly respect their skill in winning over your spawn. As for the kind hearted faction of midwives and teachers dwelling among, their number has almost totally withdrawn from sight, and soon, they will likely be no more.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 3:
			say "     Amidst all this, your cultist affinity for gravity and their pursuit of ascension continues to bear the ripest of fruits as few, if any of your loyalists can truly call themselves human any more, and they are all the happier for it. Many have started to have grown shapely digitigrade legs perfectly suited to the lush weight of their egg laden middles, or ear fins reminiscent of Olivia's. Some yet seem to have spouted tiny wings and the smattering opalescent scales, but none appear capable of reaching their full potential without you. Undeterred, they tirelessly throw themselves at their tasks, and your spawn, in the fervent hope they may ascend into Dragon Breeders one day. Their devotion to the cause is positively infectious as the new members eagerly follow their example without hesitation and washed away much of the growing divide between you cultists. Still, a degree of deference is paid to the more evolved among as now unified cultists strives to ascend together and spread the word of the goddess's coming to the unenlightened.";
		else if Morale of Arlene >= 51:
			say "     Fueled by the cults success in harvesting solar power and wind power from the island's surface, your cultists can once again enjoy a modicum of modern comforts as each of the well furnished breeder's room now hosts simple tube television, ancient VCR, and the odd hand crank assisted CD, or cassette player. Attempts have been made to try to get an internet connection up and running, but the remoteness of the area combined with the subsurface nature of the temple and the army's jamming has hampered such efforts. Still, your cultists appreciates their new accommodations as they can wait out the goddess's coming in comfort. Their personal garden has been expanded upon as tiny fruit trees sheltering in omnipresent grow lights have been brought in from the surface. Meanwhile as the wealth of the deep continues to flow in, your cultists have begun to add precious stone inlay to their hand made furniture. Though the quality varies from room-to-room the sight of flowing dragon scale arm chairs emblazoned with ruby and sapphire, or table tops capped with flowing emerald are becoming all the more common. Even the rich crimson carpet lining the main walk has been embroidered with gold dipped threads.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "     Amid this opulence, the cult's loyal well-trained Husky Bitches have begun to take over most of their master's former duties thus freeing them to delight their duly earned comfort and concentrate on the all important task of breeding. Whole teams of doting slut puppies brought from the mainland now wait on your cultist's every want or need ensuring the pillow are fluffed, craving satisfied, and carnal needs sated. To their credit, your followers never fail to lavish praise upon their pets, or reward their diligence, much to the delight of the Huskies. They seem to not only relish the fruitful state of your cultist as much as they do, but actively encourage your followers' descent into brood motherdom. A service you are of no mind to put a stop to, as the sight of your many happy cultist's burgeoning bellies and flush milky tits is a consummate pleasure.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 2:
			say "     Fed by this grandeur and faux harem of their subordinates, your dominant cultists have achieved new heights of hedonism as the bottomless hunger of their broods and the constant attention of your lesser thralls has slowly molded them into the perfect incubators for your spawn. Positively glowing under the care of their diligent feeder, these bed bound beauties' voluptuous bodies are swaddled in soft silky motherly adipose. As a thick band of doughy tallow loving cradle their arms and legs in a welcoming layer of jiggly maternal padding while plush love handles decorate their fecund hips. Their breasts have blossomed to near inhuman proportions and leaking a steady trickle of rich cream, all the better to feed the countless eggs rounding out their plush middles. Strangely though, the less fertile cultists seem to take great pride in corpulent conditions of their betters and work tirelessly to fatten them all the more. In the background, you braver cultists and their chosen draconic prowl the halls supervising the [']cows['] growth, though a part of you might feel some manner or trepidation at their influence. Their skill in managing your gluttonous broodmares urges and guiding them towards more productive ends, more than makes up for it.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 3:
			say "     Empowered by the cult's growth, and their proximity to your beatific spawn, your once human followers have nearly reached the zenith of their ascension. As many of your senior members now proudly sport wide, expansive flight capable wings clade in shimmering azure scales, regal swept back ivory horns, long perhensile spaded tails, and power digitgrade legs capped with bestial paws. While the neophytes and journeymen among them bare a piercing draconic eyes or ear fins evocative of Olivia's, thankful your cultists mutual desire to ascend to Dragon Breederdom and shared love of their changes has cemented their bond with another. As the senior members are more than eager to help instruct their junior along the path of brood motherhood, or instruct them in the carnal act of attracting and pleasing your spawn. Together, the cults number not to mention their tummies are growing by the day as their combined zeal and dutiful worship of your descendants is gradually filling the lower levels to the brim.";]

The Cultist's Chamber is west of Dragon's Causeway.

Section 4 - Mess Hall

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Mess Hall	"Mess Hall"

Mess Hall is a room.
Description of Mess Hall is "[LarderandKitchendesc]".
the scent of The Mess Hall is "A subtle smell of aromatic herbs mixed with bleach traipses about the area.".

to say LarderandKitchendesc:
	if Morale of Arlene < 10:
		say "     More of a dry pit in the earth than anything approaching a mess hall or storage site, this dark angular micro-cavern lit only by the ambient light of the Main Hall is full of craggy slate and riddled with tightly-packed stalagmites and stalactites and serves as an ad hoc repository for the cult's food and water. Most of which are left over MRE's from the supply raid hastily piled into what little free space the area has to offer. Interspersed with them are pallets of clean water either brought in by your cultists or scavenged by Arlene's crew mates during the pacification of the island. Lacking power or HVAC systems, your hardy cultists have had to largely subsist on the [']room temperature['] diet, still, access to safe regular meals is a luxury not many survivors can afford, so few complain. For all this seeming abundance, the cult's resources are rather finite and efforts are already underway to procure more, fresher goods. Or at least they would be, as the few humans dwelling here have precious little time, or the resources needed to barter for any.";
	[else if Morale of Arlene >= 11 and Morale of Arlene < 20:
		say "      With the growing numbers of cultists and dragons, the larder's expansion has become a high priority as teams of Seradovah, toiling under the guidance of Arlene's crew have worked tirelessly to hew this stable sub-section of the temple into a crude cuboid shape. While by no means pleasant to look at, as the rough stone wall and floor are pitted with claw marks, or the odd scrapes left behind by the cultist's primitive hand-made digging tools mar every ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "centimeter ";
		else:
			say "inch";
		say "of its unfinished slate surface. For all its rough edges though, the area still serves its purpose, and is now lit by a smattering of green glow sticks found among the survival gear salvaged from the raided supply ship, efforts too are underway to better organize and ration the available MRE's. While the Sea Tyrants along with Arlene's crewmates have begun dredging fresh fish, still they lack power or ventilation necessary to safely cook this serviceable fare. Instead, a slightly smaller tunnel has been rapidly cleaved into the area and vast rows drying racks and barrels of salt have brought into preserve their catch.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 21 and Morale of Arlene < 30:
		say "      Enthused by the modest success of the cults ability to catch and preserve fish, your lower priestesses have taken it upon themselves beg, borrow, or steal a number of solar panels from the mainland and combined them with those taken from your ship raid to finally bring a trickle of power into the depths. Though the output is rather meager and requires your spawn and Seradovah thralls to regularly make trips to the surface to swap out the cells, the cult now has access to simple microwaves and hot plates alongside some simple white plastic fold out tables. Both of which are now being used around the clock to purify food stuffs, or preparing the cult's simple meals as even now teams of cooks toil about the rough unfinished room to satisfy your followers['] needs. To assist them, a number of simple hand crank powered ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "have been installed about the area to provide your labors with just enough light to work in."; 
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 31 and Morale of Arlene < 40:
		say "     Enhanced by the steady influx of fresh bodies not to mention materials, the kitchen and larder are at last receiving much needed upgrades as your now better equipped followers have taken to smoothing coarse slate walls to a fine glossy sheen. While a sturdy,easy to clean white linoleum floor has laid over the bare rock, albeit haphazardly, as small lumps and bumps can be seen in places, nevertheless, your barefooted followers are thankful for the addition as the few looked forward to the many hours spent standing on the icy ground. Several canning machines and pressure cookers, additional powered solar panels taken from the mainland have been brought in as well, though they lack capacity to function on an industrial scale, the ability to preserve and in some cases export their catch is a welcome one. With them, the cult's diet has improved immensely and word of their accomplishments has even lured more than a few humans to your side. Still, power remains a constant concern as the evolving demands of your follower puts no end of strain on the fledgling power grid, so the archaic drying racks and salt are still being employed, for now at least.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 41 and Morale of Arlene < 50:
		say "     Inspired by their mounting skill in harvesting renewable power, your cultists have taken to setting up carefully hidden windmills about the island surface to finally meet their soaring demands. Though somewhat labor intensive as the never ending dance of ferrying batteries to and from the surface via the Moon Poll remains a constant fact of life, your cultists have slowly built up a considerable battery bank to help off set their demands. Meanwhile more microwaves, hotplates, and canning machines pressure cookers have been imported (or stolen) to help not just sate the blossoming cult's bottomless appetites, but for the first time, building up a true surplus of goods. At long last, your people are able to trade the oft times bland fare for scrumptious spices, valuable grains, and proper utensils instead of scaving. Thanks to this, many of your people are eating better than they did before the outbreak, and embolden by their hearty diet, the work forces has taken to adding proper lighting by staking a number of minor ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "around the area. While the linoleum floor has at last been anchor to floor industrial strength adhesive and few black non-slip pads have installed near the various workstations.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "     Your followers Huskies too have slowly been joining the cook staff, though some feared their nanite laced hair could potentially lead to unwanted transformation in likely even their fur ever made it into your cultists food. A mix of goofy looking full body hair nets and brief exposure to microwaves appears to have solved the issue, for the moment at least. Regardless, their skills are somewhat lackluster, though not for a lack of trying as the feral leaning pups are easily distracted by the sights and smells wafting through the kitchen. So for now, they have been relegated to sous-chefs, chef de partie, and impromptu waiters for the increasingly large number of bed bound breeders lounging in their personal rooms. In time though, they may yet learn to take over your cultist's duties completely, assuming you diligent followers improve their attention spans.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 51:
		say "     With the question of power at last solved thanks to a crude, but efficient relay system of Seradovah, the area has evolved into a true hot bed of actively, as the well-stocked Kitchen and Larder could put many buffets to shame as everywhere you look, the kitchen staff are hard at work preparing or preserving the rich mix of aquatic fare pulled from the by your priestesses, and the Sea Tyrants. Operating at near mechanical efficiency despite their limited tools, your workforce has arranged themselves into a thrumming assembly line of culinary delights to feed the more refined palates for your followers and spawn. While the little waste they produce is being collected for use in above ground distilleries which churn out small quantities of denatured alcohol used to keep much of the temple clean or bartered in the black markets of the warehouse district. The rest is used as part of burgeoning fertilizer cultivation project intended to lure in sea birds, and bring in fresh guano, or in some cases used as bait to catch crabs or lobster from the depths. Meanwhile, a number of creature comforts have brought into help liven up the area, as simple painting and posters decorated the playful woodland scenery now dot the glassy smooth walls of the cuboid area which provide a welcome break from the omni present polished black slate walls and ceiling alongside the gleaming white floors, and fold out kitchen tables.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "      Though few, if any humans work here anymore beyond the odd driven supervisor, or committed gourmand, as your follower's loyal and intelligent Huskies have come to take over their duties. Thanks to their master training and naturally subby mindset, the dotting slut puppies have learned to perform their new, albeit simplified duties with only a modicum of coaxing. Still there are the odd moments of where one particularly bubbly husky might hold up the line, yet pack pressure combined with their burning desire to feed and pamper their mistresses swiftly sorts out minor hiccups in the assembly line. Another time, you might have even considered expanding this lovely kennels skills and perhaps going into business one day some manner of novelty restaurant, for though you're simply content let them work and reap the benefits for the time being.";]

Mess Hall are northwest of Dragon's Causeway.

Section 5 - Treasury

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Treasury	"Treasury"

Treasury is a room.
Description of Treasury is "[Treasurydesc]".
the scent of Treasury is "The area smells cold and metallic like gale blowing across a barren field in the middle of an iron harvest.".

to say Treasurydesc:
	if Morale of Arlene < 10:
		say "     This vast cavernous section of the temple serves as the paltry beginnings of your hoard and offering chamber. Like the rest of your temple, the freshly excavated area is riddled with vast pillars of oddly smooth black slate stalactites and stalagmites jutting out of the ground like the ebony fangs of a vast long dead wyrm. Though its rough state leaves much to be desired, the raw primal quality of the seemingly smooth water-weathered walls, and the soft yellow glow of the tiny electric ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "reflecting off the unfinished stonework has a certain charm all its own. And though far from befitting a dragon of your stature, the small collection of gold coins and barnacle-encrusted silverware found during Arlene's and the Sea Tyrant's purge of the island's depths piled in the center of the room serves as a decent start for your collection. Beside which, a pile of silky grey and brown furs have been carefully laid down beside to serve as your nest, at least until such time as your cultists can find you something better.";
	[else if Morale of Arlene >= 11 and Morale of Arlene < 20:
		say "    As your cult's number grows, the extended workforce has slowly wormed its way deeper into the cold earth while steadily excavating new passageways, or refining those left behind by the Naxokaazthur. Special care though has been taken to preserve the eerie beauty of your personal chamber as your followers have carefully leveled the once craggy floor while leaving the fang-like stalactites and stalagmites leading towards your hoard-to-be intact. With the aid of some cleverly positioned mirrors and tactful readjustment of the electric ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "have further enhanced the spectacular shadows cast by the glass smooth half pillars while drawing the focus of the available light upon your petty hoard of gold coins and barnacle encrusted silver nesting the center of the room. Though a few meager hand crafted bauble hewn from wave polished glass, and tide smooth rock crudely worked into your likeness alongside a number of watches and simple rings have been to the pile as offering to you.";
		say "     Despite the lowly nature of your followers tithe to your draconic splendor, a covetous sliver of your coldblooded mind nevertheless appreciates their attempt at honoring their better. Your bedding too, though you hesitate to call it such, has been slightly improved upon with the additional layers of satin grey and brown furs. Looking at them more closely though, it would be hard not to see the hasty cuts jagged running along the edges, or the lingering uniform stitch marks left on their undersides as some hidden layer of fabric were once sown on the inside. Judging by the consistent nature of these marks, you surmise these were once coats belonging to your cults, or found by your followers on an excursion to the mainland. Regardless of their origin, they still make a pleasant, if primitive nest.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 21 and Morale of Arlene < 30:
		say "     Driven by their growing zeal and aided by the gradually trickle of materials flowing into the cult's possession, you followers have made a concerted effort has been made to smooth the tough slate floor of the treasury to a lustrous mirror while preserving the gentle fluted structure of the odd stalactites and stalagmites decorating the area. This stunning visual effect is further enhanced by the addition a more potent set of mirror backed electric ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "bathing the area in a welcoming white light. Together with the stone's preternatural sheen, the walkway leading to your mounting hoard has obtained a measure of mirror-esque qualities as the black glossy seems to reflect the image of those standing upon it their left and right. Meanwhile the toothy shadowy quality of The Treasury peripheries has left intact thanks to some adjustment of mirrors sequestered about the area.";
		say "     Your hoard too has been expanded upon as they tireless searches of Sea Tyrants and calculated raids of your priestesses have brought in a generous trickle of abyssal wealth, mostly in the treasure looted the soft rubes of Atlantis, or pulled from clutches of some long lost treasure ships bound for the old world in a bygone age. Buoyed by their bounty, the once pathetic pile of coins and barnacle encrusted silverware now reaches up to your tauric ankles and is joined by raw meteoric emeralds, and wave polish moonstone. Beside them, more offerings carved from driftwood festooned with beach glass or hewed mother of pearl have been passably into your rough draconic likeness, though the quality leaves much to be desired. The earnest attempts at honoring the better are not lost on you, and a few even show a modicum of promise. While your nest now hosts wider selection of furs ranging for pearly white, to lustrous ebony, chocolate browns, and lustrous gold, though the sources vary many appear to have once part of taxidermied museum exhibit at least going by their vague shape.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 31 and Morale of Arlene < 40:
		say "      Glutted with fresh plunder, your cultists and to a lesser extent your draconic spawn along with the Seradovah have begun to post guards outside The Treasury. Though few in the cult believe anyone outside their blessed ranks has any true inkling as to the whereabouts of your temple, or its wealth. Much less would be foolish enough to steal from you, let alone mount an assault on these hallowed grounds. The sheer size of the building pile of glittering gold, precious gems, barnacle encrusted silverware stacked all the way to your knees nevertheless warrants some manner of protection. To that end, a mix of human and draconic guards now stand watch outside, gifted with spare PHASRs and MAD guns, and armoured in bodygloves, they make for an imposing, if adhoc guardians. Their presence too provides your followers with an added sense of security as proximity to the temple's Main Hall and Moon Pool ensures no one can enter into your sanctum unopposed. Meanwhile, the pillars dotting the area offer simple but effective cover for the defenders should some misguided soul ever dare to defile this place.";
		say "      In recognition for their service, and your benevolent foresight in providing them with the tools needed to defend themselves, your cultists have crafted a number of passable idols to commemorate the creation of this temple guard in the form of carved slate inlay the abalone shell figures fashioned into the general shape of your talons or fangs and placed amid your hoard. Though of humble origins, their shimmering surfaces are rather pleasing to the eyes and demonstrates your follower's growing skill with stone cutting and lapidary work. As the pillars surrounding the have tasteful bands of gold carefully worked into their gloss fluted surfaces, along with a pathway made of rich crimson jasper tiles. Your bedding too has been improved as your follower gradually begun to refine then stitch the disparate pelts into several large mono-colored quilts stuffed with warm supple down.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 41 and Morale of Arlene < 50:
		say "     With the growing pomp and splendor of your temple, your cultists have added a few creature comforts to your nest in the form of large hand sewn throw pillows spun from purple silk. Along their edges, thick lustrous tassels of gold laced silk have been carefully woven into supple fabric. Stuffed to the brim with plush down, these pleasant additions to your nest can easily accommodate your towering physique with ease. Hidden within them though, are a number of battery powered heating pads connected sturdy looking toggles dyed a metallic purple have sown beside the tassels. Your fur blankets have received a similar treatment from your cultists, their dials are a bit more obvious, though no less functional. Meanwhile, The Treasury proper has received a fresh stone polish to truly bring out the slate's shine and better highlight a gentle wave like quality of the natural rock's grain. The jasper walkway leading toward the chest high pile of plunder and various offerings left to you in the center of the room too has been further refined to bring out the striking shimmer of the stone imparted by the electric ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "torches ";
		else:
			say "lanterns ";
		say "dotting the area.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "     Your temple guard meanwhile have added a number of Husky Bitches to the ranks, though far intimidating, the quad breasted slut puppies cuddly bodies nevertheless look rather fetching in their bodygloves. As the tight latex light fabric supports and coddles their delectable D-cup and dainty C-cups in its taut embrace. While the plush impression of their perpetually heat flushed puppy adds a nice bit of eye candy for the guard and fresh faced novices as they watch them happily prowl the entryway to The Treasury. Few though are under any allusions that in the event of an incursion they will be much help, still the additional PHASRs could help tip the scales in the cults favor one day. That said, their loyalty to their mistresses and heightened senses make them effective guard dogs if nothing.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 2:
			say "     With the rising penchant for gluttony and affinity for gravity infecting your flock, your human temple guards have lost most of their combat effectiveness as their pudgy latex wrapped bodies would look more like a home on a BBW dominatrix, then a supposed protector of your flock. Though they can still fire a PHASR if need be, few have any real confidence your formerly fierce fighters could stand much of a chance in a drawn out engagement. Instead, your human auxiliaries have begun cultivating their bodies' ability to produce mothers milk and now serve a milky medics or fonts of convenient [']release['] for your spawn and their Seradoavah partners. Untested as they may be, morale among the draconic protectors has never been higher. Besides, you can't say you don't enjoy the spectacle of the chubby gravid breeders parading their curvaceous bumps and ripe milky latex wrapped about the grounds either. ";
		else if Loyalty	 of Cultists is 3:
			say "     Empowered by their draconic ascension, the guard's human contingent has been fully replaced by demi-dragon cultists and has been made all the stronger for it. As only the most evolved and driven of your followers are now allowed to serve alongside the Seradovah and your spawn, nearing the pinnacle of their ascension each guard is graced with cute little wings, thick blue spaded tail almost as long as they are tall. Clad in form fitting bodygloves that neatly hug their beastly digitigrade legs and toned draconic arms, while highlighting their tight athletic build giving them an impressive yet intimidating figure. That is further enhanced by sight of their gleaming horns and molten draconic eyes decorating their still somewhat human faces. Under their watchful gaze, your cultists have never felt safer and strive to emulate their example in the fervent hope they too may ascend to the same lofty heights one day.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 51:
		say "     Overflowing with treasure, your admirable hoard is almost worthy of your draconic majesty as almost ever ";
		if "Touched by Madness" is listed in feats of Player:
			say "centimeter ";
		else:
			say "inch ";
		say "of the smooth and profoundly lustrous slate treasury is blanketed in gold coins, meteoric gemstones, and ancient silverware pulled or raided from the depths. Almost large enough for you to swim in, the sheer mountain dotting the area can barely accommodate these various offerings and idols fashioned in your image by your followers. Though their quality varies for lewd statues of your draconic splendor in full repose hewed from chunks of polished moonstone, to simple slate claws inlaid with mother of pear, the minor bauble nevertheless serve as joysome reminds of your cults devotion to you and how far they've come from. As it stands barely any space remains for your massive heated silky purple body pillows, or collection of warming fur quilts, forcing your cultists to move them onto the center of jasper walkway. Still the pleasant mix of color and primal shadow images cast by the smooth slate and pillar along the area's fringes more than makes up for the slight loss of privacy.";
		if Loyalty of Cultists is 1:
			say "     As for your temple guards, the humans have been completely replaced with loyal Husky Bitches as their trainers have all retired to the chamber to focus on the all important task of motherhood. Not a soul has complained about these changes though, as the doting slut puppies have become ever more protective of their mistresses in their preferred condition. And what they lack in skill compared to your human followers, they make up for it in numbers and devotion as the guards numbers have more than doubled since the humans stepped down. Besides the adorable looks on their faces as they scan the area for threats, the sensual nature of their form fitting bodyglove has done wonders for the cultist's morale. As none among them are immune to the heavenly sight of quad breast lovingly swaddled in pristine black latex, or inviting bulge of their puppy pus staining against the confines of uniform while they patrol the entrance to The Treasury.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 2:
			say "    While the total descent of your cultist into ravenous brood motherdom, has taken its toll on your human guards as they've almost completely devolved into doting feeders or domineering breeders. Those still willing and able to walk are now little more than cooing milk cows or clutch mad sows who do little more than cater to your descent needs while they bask in the glorious sight of the resplendent fecund bodies. Another time, you might have chastised them for their slothfulness, yet your flight is all the happier for their presence as the many hours on lookout for an attack that will, in all likelihood, never come wears down upon them. At least with now the company of their voluptuous companions, the tediums of the long watch are lessened for all.";
		else if Loyalty of Cultists is 3:
			say "     Meanwhile, your elite temple guards are stronger than ever as the ranks of your ascending draconic mothers-to-be continue to grow by the day as ever more for your driven cultist to take up arms to proudly defend their less evolved peers. Some even choose to serve through their ever more frequent pregnancies, though you suspect this desire is not fully born of altruism as the gravid demi-dragons seem to enjoy not only the extra attention paid to them by your spawn while on watch. As more than once, you've caught one more of them sneaking off together to who knows where. But the chance to chance to show off their growing curves in tight latex bodyglove to the new recruits as they arrive, and bask in the looks of profound awe they receives from the neophytes as they drink in the sight of their changing body and bountiful bumps.";]

The Treasury is the north of Dragon's Causeway.

Section 6 - Tiamat's Chapel

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Tiamat's Chapel	"Tiamat's Chapel"

Tiamat's Chapel is a room.
Description of Tiamat's Chapel is "[thechapeldesc]".
the scent of Tiamat's Chapel is "Replete with the scents of coldblodded desire and alien rock.".

to say thechapeldesc:
	if Morale of Arlene < 10:
		say "      More unveiled then excavated, the rough nascent Chapel to Tiamat and Kai-Monah seems to be comprised, at least partially, of an entirely different type of rock compared to the rest of them temple as streaks of deep metallic green can be seen poking through the jet black slate dotting the oft times spikey and oblong-shaped room. Oddly glossy, and almost wet to both the look and touch, these usually glowing streaks of stone are completely impervious to any attempts at removing them, while the nearby native rock can easily be peeled back by hand, almost as if the unusual strata worming its way through this section of the temple wishes to be uncovered. Despite this, the process is slow, as disposing of the waste stone takes time, yet even now a number of rough shapes can be seen poking through. To your many eyes, these veins of exotic rock resemble serpentine scales coiling about the area like eels slinking through some abyssal kelp forest, all which seem to head back toward the rear of this craggy cavernous pit. Strangely enthused by the find, Harbinger has taken to leading the Seradovah's excavation. Despite the mild protests of your priestess, urging hir to focus on more important areas like the Moon Pool or the Cultist's Chambers, shi remains steadfast in hir efforts. Only time will tell if hir venture is worthwhile though, or a waste of resources. Regardless, this unusual space still serves as an adequate site for Arlene and Harbinger's hurried sermons as they preach the coming of Tiamat and your eventual ascension.";
	[else if Morale of Arlene >= 11 and Morale of Arlene < 20:
		say "     As the day wears on, the slow unveiling and expansion of the Chapel has encountered a snag of sorts as the Seradovah assigned to this have hit a wall of impenetrable glowing green stone embedded around the pyramid shaped entrance to this primal Chapel. Undeterred, the thrallish works have instead begun following this seam of glossy emerald as they carefully peel back the layers of strangely soft slate to reveal more of this anomalous substance flowing outwards in all directions. Peering closely at it, you can see vein-like pules or subtle scale patterning shimmering along the edges of the unnaturally level seams, almost if it were grown or poured here by some unseen hand. No matter its origins, this serpentine stone has drawn the eyes of your cultists as many can't help but marvel at the five sided spiral taking shape sprawling outwards along prismatic veins of equally impenetrable green, blue, red, white, and black rock a center pillar bejeweled in a vibrant mixture of the holy hues.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 21 and Morale of Arlene < 30:
		say "     After much sweat and toil, the true shape of The Chapel has begun to emerge as more of the too-soft slate has been peeled back to reveal the first true hint of The Chapel's size, and form. Easily larger than most single story ranch style houses, the spiraling mix of green, blue, red, white, and black rock sprawling outwards like the arms of a distant pinwheel galaxy. Though work still needs to be done to remove and dispose of the last chucks of slate covering the peripheries of this abyssal blessing, a rough image of draconic serpentine heads boring into the earth has begun to emerge. Meanwhile at the core is the Chapal, a smooth cylindrical pillar composed of a chaotic swirl of the goddesses's favored colors has been fully revealed. Utterly impervious to the harm and smoother than any glass, this edifice has become the nesting site of Harbinger and many of hir Seradovah thrall's eggs, from here, shi preaches the beatific word of the goddess's arrival, joys of submitting to her will, or provides succor to those who wish to part of hir eternal bounty. While Arlene has been having rotating sermon about the five head wing of The Chapel as shi instills within your follower a proper love of breeding and respect for your name.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 31 and Morale of Arlene < 40:
		say "    Freed from the last vestiges of its rocky womb, the vast multi-colored Chapel true form is a wondrous sight to behold as five distinct sections are arrayed around a massive central pillar composed of green, blue, red, white, and black stone. Each one of these [']wings['] seem to have almost been shaped or perhaps growing it the curvy serpentine draconic heads that seem to bathe the area in an omnipresent light. Their seemingly impregnable stone surfaces, though impossibly smooth to the touch, possesses subtle teardrop shaped scaly emblazoned upon it and seems to thrum ever-so-slightly, as if the very rock could spring to life at any moment. Enthralled by its discovery, your cultist and draconic spawn have begun flocking to The Chapel in ever greater numbers, both hear the good word of Tiamat's coming alongside the promises of your own ascension, and seek succor from Harbinger."; 
		say "     As the buxom Seradovah queen has found hir calling in providing chaplain services to your flock, tender pillow to rest their heads on after a hard day of service, or sympathetic ear to your followers in their rare moments of doubt. More than a few of your followers have even begun to openly expressed an interest in attempting to cross the rubicon and joining hir as queens themselves, others too have become nursery staff for the subby breeders growing hoards of eggs slumbering about the area. While Arlene still has has how hir own minor sermons from time-to-time, your priestess has slowly been eschewing going to The Chapel altogether, instead preferring to preach  hir message of brood motherdom and exaltation of your flight in the Main Hall, or from the comforts of hir own chambers.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 41 and Morale of Arlene < 50:
		say "     Lavished with the hard earned comforts the cult has slowly accrued from the depths, or bartered from the mainland, The Chapel proper has been furnished with an expansive mix of burnt mahogany pews. Each one is inscribed with a faux-scale pattern modeled after the unusual teardrop shaped scales found along the walls and have been arrayed around the central. While the tasteful image of draconic paws have been painstakingly carved into the feet of each pew and series of carefully polished sections of mother-of-pearl have been inlaid along the scything talons. A number of ponderously large silky white kneeling pillows have been carefully placed along the spiraling green, blue, red, white, and black wings of The Chapel's five dragon head annexes sprawling outwards from the central pillar. Each one is easily able to accommodate not just your draconic spawn's tauric bodies, but the lengthy coils of the Seradovha in the rare moment Harbinger dames to have them sit in on hir sermons.";
		say "     Hir eggs too, along with those laid by the lesser Seradovah, and in cases those whelped by your followers have been a similar honor as the large pearly ovoid ovum now comfortably rest upon modest throw pillows as well. Even the hub of activity, many of your followers have started to come in their off hours to pray to Tiamat, or to glut themselves of Harbingers eternal bounty. A service the milky naga is more than happy to provide as the lewd chaplain takes great pride in reassuring the masses, or extolling the virtues of submission to your flock's draconic masters. Arlene though, has mostly abandoned the Chapel and only appears in the increasingly rare instances she is summoned by its caretaker, or to aid in the inductions of new members. Otherwise, your priestess has more or less retreated to the Main Hall and the comforts of hir own personal chambers where continues to spread the word of your coming ascension, and extolls the glory of dragonkind.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 51:
		say "      Festooned with abyssal wealth, Taimat's expensive Chapel is well on its way to rivaling the mega churches of the deep south, if not in size, then at least in opulence, as offering in the for ancient doubloons and meteoric gemstones litters the halls and alcoves of the five headed dragon chapel. Most are neatly sorted along the spiraling green, blue, red, white, and black wings of The Chapel as offerings to the multi head goddess's various chromatic servants. Though special attention seems to have been paid to the blue section of the temple, likely in homage to the Cruel Sea Tyrants who collected this bounty from the depths and first broke ground on the temple all those many days ago. The sea of gold coins is largely situated around the central spire at the heart of the temple along the many Seradovah pearly eggs laid by Harbinger and your followers. While the burnt mahogany pew have had soft velvety black cushions added to them, and number of expertly cut gemstones have be carefully inlaid upon the scales patterns worked into them.";
		say "    To the casual eye, these lustrous jewels almost perfectly mimic the glowing otherworld stone lining the chapel, yet no amount of lapidary work properly captures the quasi-organic thrumming of the luminescent stone comprising The Chapel. More pillows too have been added to the various annexes to accommodate your spawn's increased presence as come to hear the voice of the goddess's chosen Seradovah, or share a not-so-private moment with favored humans and obedient naga thralls within these hallowed walls. As for Arlene, shi has totally abandoned Chapel in favor of the lush comforts of hir own quarters and the more neutral ground of Main Hall. Though some of the old guard miss hir presence, Harbinger is now free to extoll the virtues of submission to goddess's will, and yours on hir own terms. Though hir role as chaplain and occasional confessor remains the greatest draws, as you cults have come to treasure their time in hir coils or the lovely opportunity to sample hir delectable creams. Many openly beg for the chance to join hir as a fellow queen, so they may better serve as the five heads commands.";]
		
Tiamat's Chapel is southeast of Dragon's Causeway.

Section 7- Priestess's Chamber

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Priestess's Chamber	"Priestess's Chamber"

Priestess's Chamber is a room.
Description of Priestess's Chamber is "[PriestessChamberdesc]".
the scent of The Priestess's Chamber is "Arlene's room smells of old leather, wood polish, and brine.".

to say PriestessChamberdesc:
	if Morale of Arlene < 10:
		say "       Despite the hurried nature of your cults ascension, special care has been to insure your priestess's spherical accommodations are befitting your chosen mouthpiece and herald of your ascension as Arlene's quaint but spacious quarters are leagues above those provided to your human followers. The somewhat-smoothed slate floors are festooned with all manner of thick fluffy pelts taken from the great purge of the island undertaken by the hir crew and the Naxokaazthur. A crude metal four poster bed barely big enough for hir to sleep on and likely pulled from the depths of the warehouse district has been placed in the rear of the room and painted with a striking crimson, while a supple sheet of creamy white velvet accompanied by several throw pillows are atop it. Draped along the rough unfinished walls of hir chamber at even intervals are a number of simple blue and white banners with gold emblazoned with a simple outline of your draconic head, while a number of battery-powered prop lights fashioned into the shape of waist high wrought iron candelabras have been placed about hir living space, bathing these cavernous quarters in a soft yellow-orange glow.";
	[else if Morale of Arlene >= 11 and Morale of Arlene < 20:
		say "     Emboldened by the rush of fresh recruits and material, Arlene has taken great care to ensure hir chambers reflect the cult's rising status and hir own position as your mouthpiece. Though a part of you might once have chafed at the waste of resources and woman hours spent on improving hir dwelling, it would not reflect on you to have your priestess's sleep on rags like a common beggar. To that end, your cults have toiled long and hard to smooth out the few remaining rough edges of Arlene's chamber while doing their best to preserve some of the primal stalactites hanging overhand. Hir crude fur carpets too, have been cut and sewn into a proper rug that covers much of the area, undeniably pleasing to walk on, the warm plush pelts feel profoundly wondrous beneath your paws as the silky fur loving caresses your pads with each step you take. Hir bed frame to has been replaced with a far larger high back piece of varnished redwood, likely taken from some showroom floor, or a stolen from the Warehouse District.";
		say "     Though you doubt it could hold your majestic tauric weight for more than an instant, the expansive bit of furniture is more than serviceable for your buxom priestess's needs. While pillows remain the same, hir sheets have been swapped for a cream velour that seem to simmer with an almost opalescent quality in the false candle light of battery powered candelabras. Fresh golden banners with silver laces fashioned in the image of hir own resplendent bump now serve as a potent reminder of both hir's and the cult's ultimate purpose. Beside them, and the effigies of your own draconic visage, as well as a number of off-white folding tables and chairs have been placed along the western edges of hir room. Atop them, are a number of brown leather backed ledgers, simple abacus, and plain black ball point pens have been carelessly tossed down. Most detail the cult's current supplies situation, though some contain notes on possible treasure sites beneath the waves, or raidable locations along the shore, or at least you assume as much as Arlene's handwriting, not mention hir spelling, leaves much to be desired.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 21 and Morale of Arlene < 30:
		say "     Furnished with the latest fineries taken from the depths or bartered from the mainland, Arlene continues to divert a non-insubstantial of the cult's assets and workforce to improve hir dwelling, all of which she claims is meant to show power and the prestige of hir draconic masters. As your greedy priestess has ordered your followers to remove the cheap plastic furniture situated along the western edges of hir abode and import a proper wooden desk, made of polished opalized wood and ergonomic black leather office chair for hir own personal use. To your eyes, the gleaming citrine brown surface laced a prismatic band of blue, green, and white crystal shimmers invitingly in the gentle orange-yellow glow of hir waist high wrought iron candelabras. Hir abacus too has been replaced with a proper calculator while a few old black berry phones have to hir collection of ledgers. Hir handwriting or whatever shi call hir horrid chicken scratch though remains as awful as ever as the few open books can attest.";
		say "     Though as the cults needs continue to expand your budding logistician, has added several simple triple tiered black bookshelves along the eastern side of hir chamber. Hir varnished redwood bed now hosts a new set of fluffy white stain pillows that blend in nicely with the cream alabaster velour sheets decorating hir sleeping space. While fresh banners have been to hir collection as intermingling between the blue and gold effigies of your draconic skull, black and silver laced renditions of hir prominent bump, are joined by purple and yellow icons woven into the shape of the Naxokaazthur's webbed paws. Hir vast collection of pelt rugs have been slightly readjusted to create a stone walkway of sorts connecting hir bed, table, and bookcases. Polished to a near glassy sheen, the stone natural grain has taken a wavy quality evocative damascus steel, or the hamon line of some Japanese blade.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 31 and Morale of Arlene < 40:
		say "     Spoiled by the doting attentions of your flock, and the recent influx of wealth pulled from the depths or raided from the wider world, Arlene has begun to spend more and more time in the growing comforts of hir chamber's. As moderate a number of fanciful pieces of restored silver and large circular dining table working into the image of sprawling to squat gnarled tree made from several sections of turned burl with thick glass table top has been placed at the center of hir. Several plain high backed chairs made of some dense hardwood, stained a rich wine red and embossed with thick silky grey cushions have been arrayed around, only one shows any sign of being sat in. Hir opalized wood desks set along the western section of hir abode though are slowly being swallowed in a mountain of books, sadly hir penmanship and horrid spelling makes it difficult to pull useful information from their pages. ";
		say "     Strangely, many appear to contain reference hir dreams, or have long winded idle musing regarding the changes to hir body since becoming your priestess. Hir black bookcases situated along the eastern half of hir room are steadily overflowing with similar tomes, alongside a few black berries, and the latest flip phones which have been haphazardly stacked in unremarkable brown woven baskets. While hir collection of banners depicting your draconic skull, hir blushing baby bump, and the Naxokaazthur's paw remain unchanged, a pair davenport built from polished rosewood and inlaid with manner of spiral black enamel evocative of narwhal horn have been placed beside hir bed. One appears to be playing host crystal glass decanter, and collection of cobalt blue glass set atop a silver platter, while a number of sheets of blank vellum and ballpoint pens have been haphazardly spread about the rest.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 41 and Morale of Arlene < 50:
		say "     Fed with fresh plunder, Arlene's chambers have slowly become host to a small hoard of rough gemstones and fancy bejeweled fountain pens, dotting hir desk and bookshelves. Naturally, this pittance of a treasure pales in comparison to the vast mountain of riches pooling in The Treasury, as these meager, forgettable bobbles are little more than fancy paper weight, or symbols of office. As no true dragon of your stature could be dead allowing their chosen mouthpiece to wield mundane tools for long, it is thus only fitting that your priestess should bare such trinkets. From the looks of it, shi's seems to be putting them to good use as countless empty bottle ink can be seen tucked underneath hir opalized wood desks situated along the western half of hir room. Atop them are thick walls of ledgers, many of which contain notes on the cults' resources and consumption, alongside recountings of hir own tainted dreams. Or at least, you think that's what they as your priestess's piss poor handwriting might as well be detailing recipes of gazpacho going by the horrid scrawl blighting the pages.";
		say "     Hir black bookcase fares little better as the sheer weight of text has started to make the bend in places; only the aid of hir hardwood davenports to catch the overflow prevents them from collapsing. Meanwhile, you ravenous priestess's has begun have constant steam of fresh meals delivered to hir abode, even now, hir turned burl table circular topped by a thick sheet of glass is laden with platters of steaming fish, glistening exotic fruits, and jugs of sweet smelling juices. Little has been done to hir hardwood bed covered throw pillows and creamy alabaster sheets along banner displaying the blue and gold renditions of your draconic skull, the black and silver laced effigies of hir blushing baby bump, and purple and yellow depictions of the Naxokaazthur's paw. Though you have noticed a slight sag in hir mattress, and the deepening groove in the silky grey pillow decorating hir favorite chair.";
	else if Morale of Arlene >= 51:
		say "     Lavished with unbridled wealth of your abyssal cult, Arlene's chambers are host to an impressive hoard of gold coins and meteoric gemstone pulled from the depths of your servants over the course of these many days. Though most is swiftly deposited into The Treasury, many of your draconic spawn have to come and leave small offerings to your priestess in gratitude for hir tireless divination, and to pay homage to your patron for her continued favor. As such a large pile of riches bigger than several kiddy pools are wide and as tall as a yoga ball now fills the center of Arlene's chamber. Openly smitten with its presence, your greedy priestess has had hir table and bed removed so that shi may bask atop it like a miserly wyrm while shi doles out commands to your cults. Most of which involve taking notes for hir, or reading off reports detailing the cult's day-to-day functions or needs. To this end, teams of scribes and servants have been brought into assist hir this task and insure the cult's continued wellbeing."; 
		say "     Even now, several human clusters around Arlene, hir hardwood desks, black bookcases, and davenports as they pour through the shoddily written ledgers while compiling new streamlined volumes. A few though seem rather interested in hir collection of electronics, and oddly enough try to keep their screens out of your eyesight as they fiddle with them. Oddly, most of the banners once decorating hir chamber have been removed save for those depicting Arlene's gravid tummy, what more they seem to have been embellished with a smattering of stretch marks while simple outline of a dragon's paw have been sown about around the banner's [']navel[']. Though such minor details matter little to you, as hir devotion to you and cause remain absolute, so for the moment, you've chosen to overlook hir self-indulgent streaks.";]
		
The Priestess's Chamber is east of Dragon's Causeway.


Section 4 - Sandbar

Table of GameRoomIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Sandbar	"Sandbar"

Sandbar is a room.
Description of Sandbar is "[Sandbardesc]".
The scent of Sandbar is "Idly sniffing air around, your senses are greeted by the coiling scents of briny ocean spray, and the sickeningly sweet subtle tangs of abyssal decay wafting from the ubiquitous caves dotting the area.".

to say Sandbardesc:
	say "     Circumscribing much of the Island's western fringes, this thin stretch of fine yellow sand offers little in the way of cover from the rough offshore breezes and pounding waves pouring towards the coast. Occasionally, the soft shimmering sediment gives way to the odd bit of driftwood, or brightly-colored flotsam and jetsam poking through the smooth golden grains in irregular intervals. Most is little more than sea polished glass intersperced with the battered husks of colorful unidentifiable plastic. Yet as the winds shift, and tiny dust devils begin to dance along the dunes, you can spy the odd corroded shell of some wave-lashed machinery mixed in with the common debris. Unlike the rest of litter polluting the island's windward side, these pitted fragments of metal and sun-damaged rubber appear to be a more recent addition to the island's shores as here and there you can still spot signs of partial serial numbers and maker's marks emblazoned upon. Ringing these polluted dunes, are a number of craggy hills and half-collapsed caverns winding their way down into the depths.";

Sandbar is east of Pirate Island.


Dragon Temple Map ends here.